I"Ò5<p>Some time ago, I had to make a project that required <strong>syntax highlighting</strong> - luckily I wasnâ€™t the one who had to make that part. However the version used in the project was more complicated - so I decided to make a tutorial that will teach you how to make a <em>basic</em> syntax highlighter (with <strong>Regex</strong>).</p>

<p>Iâ€™ll be using the <strong>RichTextBox</strong> control - using the simple <strong>TextBox</strong> might seem to be better but itâ€™s kinda difficult to implement the word coloring function without getting into other troubles.</p>

<p>Anyhow it needs to be improved - I tried to keep things as simple as possible. This program is just to show you the basic idea behind a syntax highlighter.</p>

